---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Kallin Nagelberg — software engineer and engineering leader, civic-tech builder, high-leverage with AI tooling." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About</h1>
			<p>
				I'm Kallin Nagelberg — a software engineer and engineering leader with
				15+ years building platforms and the teams behind them. By day I'm a
				Senior Software Engineer at <a href="https://wiza.co">Wiza</a>; before
				that I was a Director of Engineering. I'm a full-stack generalist
				(Ruby, Python, AWS) who's found a lot of leverage in AI tooling lately.
			</p>
			<p>
				The thread I keep coming back to outside of work is <strong>civic tech</strong> —
				making government data legible. I recently built
				<a href="https://glowing-torte-c0235a.netlify.app/">an interactive tool to trace Ontario's $244B budget</a>,
				tagging every figure by how transparent its source actually is, and I'm
				doing early work on <a href="https://citizens.run/">citizens.run</a>,
				which helps people understand the weight of their vote. I think AI has
				quietly made a new kind of civic analysis possible, and that's where a
				lot of my curiosity points right now.
			</p>
			<p>
				This blog is where I write things down — what I'm learning, what I'm
				building, and the occasional reality-adjacent thought.
			</p>
			<p>Find me elsewhere:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://github.com/Kallin">GitHub</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kallin/">LinkedIn</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/15580883-kallin-nagelberg">GoodReads</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://www.codingame.com/profile/4b1d61768cee9c0433fa188b757ef9535296954">CodinGame</a></li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Reach out on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kallin/">LinkedIn</a>
				or at the email in the footer.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
